The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 October is 3,921 (453.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 October, there were 295 new confirmed cases (34.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 September, there were 208 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 42% ( 87 extra cases).
